<p class="p">Accumulating evidence has begun to show that climate change is altering the spread and distribution of parasitic diseases and their associated vectors.
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref rid="bibr19-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">19</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr29-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">29</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr31-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">31</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr40-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">40</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr48-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">48</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr67-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">67</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr84-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">84</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr99-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">99</xref>
  <xref rid="bibr100-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref"/>
  <xref rid="bibr101-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref"/>â€“
  <xref rid="bibr102-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">102</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr104-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">104</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr105-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">105</xref>
 </sup> This poses both a direct and indirect threat to human quality of life. Directly, these parasites may have the ability to infect a greater number of people through emergence and reemergence in areas made hospitable by a changing climate.
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref rid="bibr19-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">19</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr20-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">20</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr25-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">25</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr40-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">40</xref>
 </sup> Indirectly, advancement and development of communities may slow due to infection of crops and livestock which could hinder, or even stifle, economic growth.
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref rid="bibr99-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">99</xref>,
  <xref rid="bibr106-1178633617732296" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">106</xref>
 </sup>
</p>
